e England":"Weston under Lizard, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Weston, Staffordshire, England":"Weston, Staffordshire, England"},"nl":{"1048–1130":"1048–1130","1047–1078":"1047–1078","1040–1078":"1040–1078","1065–1120":"1065–1120","1073–1126":"1073–1126","1066":"1066","1120":"1120","1065":"1065","1130":"1130","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","1073":"1073","1040":"1040","1106":"1106","1126":"1126","1048":"1048","1047":"1047","Abt 1077":"circa 1077","1078":"1078","about 1065":"circa 1065","Newton, Staffordshire, England":"Newton, Staffordshire, England","Weston Under Lizard Staffordshire England":"Weston under Lizard, Staffordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Weston, Staffordshire, England":"Weston, Staffordshire, England"},"en":{"1048–1130":"1048–1130","1047–1078":"1047–1078","1040–1078":"1040–1078","1065–1120":"1065–1120","1073–1126":"1073–1126","1066":"1066","1120":"1120","1065":"1065","1130":"1130","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","1073":"1073","1040":"1040","1106":"1106","1126":"1126","1048":"1048","1047":"1047","Abt 1077":"about 1077","1078":"1078","about 1065":"about 1065","Newton, Staffordshire, England":"Newton, Staffordshire, England","Weston Under Lizard Staffordshire England":"Weston under Lizard, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Weston, Staffordshire, England":"Weston, Staffordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Agatha","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of   Agnes   and   Agatha ."],"variants":[{"name":"Agnes","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705182,"age":18,"year":"1066","julianDay":2110409,"title":"Battle of Hastings","description":"Battle of Hastings was fought between the Norman-French army and the battle-wary English army on October 14, 1066. Duke William of Normandy believed he was the rightful king rather than Harold, who had been crowned king several months earlier. Harold was killed in battle and William was crowned king on Christmas Day 1066.","url":"https://www.english-heritage.org.uk/learn/1066-and-the-norman-conquest/what-happened-battle-hastings/","urlTitle":"English Heritage - Battle of Hastings","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705183,"age":38,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705184,"age":48,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705185,"age":58,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Agatha was born in 1048, in Weston, Staffordshire, England. She married Urnoi de Weston about 1077, in Weston, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1130, in her hometown, at the age of 82."},"et":{"1048–1130":"1048–1130","1047–1078":"1047–1078","1040–1078":"1040–1078","1065–1120":"1065–1120","1073–1126":"1073–1126","1066":"1066","1120":"1120","1065":"1065","1130":"1130","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","1073":"1073","1040":"1040","1106":"1106","1126":"1126","1048":"1048","1047":"1047","Abt 1077":"umbes 1077","1078":"1078","about 1065":"umbes 1065","Newton, Staffordshire, England":"Newton, Staffordshire, England","Weston Under Lizard Staffordshire England":"Weston under Lizard, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Weston, Staffordshire, England":"Weston, Staffordshire, England"},"fi":{"1048–1130":"1048–1130","1047–1078":"1047–1078","1040–1078":"1040–1078","1065–1120":"1065–1120","1073–1126":"1073–1126","1066":"1066","1120":"1120","1065":"1065","1130":"1130","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","1073":"1073","1040":"1040","1106":"1106","1126":"1126","1048":"1048","1047":"1047","Abt 1077":"noin 1077","1078":"1078","about 1065":"noin 1065","Newton, Staffordshire, England":"Newton, Staffordshire, England","Weston Under Lizard Staffordshire England":"Weston under Lizard, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Weston, Staffordshire, England":"Weston, Staffordshire, England"},"fr":{"1048–1130":"1048–1130","1047–1078":"1047–1078","1040–1078":"1040–1078","1065–1120":"1065–1120","1073–1126":"1073–1126","1066":"1066","1120":"1120","1065":"1065","1130":"1130","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","1073":"1073","1040":"1040","1106":"1106","1126":"1126","1048":"1048